HEADWORD: Fraunhofer lines
<hw>Fraun"ho*fer lines`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>.
<fld>(Physics.)</fld> <def>The lines of the spectrum; especially and
properly, the dark lines of the solar spectrum, so called because first
accurately observed and interpreted by
<person><etsep>Fraunhofer</etsep></person>, a German
physicist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fraxin</ent>⟦br⟧
